               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t18300916-43-off230-c381" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-43-defend470 t18300916-43-off230 t18300916-43-verdict233"></join>
         
               <p>1508. 
               
                  <persName id="t18300916-43-defend470" type="defendantName">
                     WILLIAM 
                     SHEARMAN
                  <interp inst="t18300916-43-defend470" type="surname" value="SHEARMAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-43-defend470" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-43-defend470" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-43-defend470" type="age" value="22"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t18300916-43-off230" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18300916-43-off230" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-43-off230" type="offenceSubcategory" value="pocketpicking"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18300916-43-cd231" type="crimeDate">21st of August</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-43-off230 t18300916-43-cd231"></join>, 1 handkerchief, value 3s., the goods of a certain man unknown, from his person
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300916-43-person471">
                  JOHN 
                  ANDERSON
               <interp inst="t18300916-43-person471" type="surname" value="ANDERSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-43-person471" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-43-person471" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 21st of August, I saw the prisoner in <placeName id="t18300916-43-crimeloc232">St. James'-street, Piccadilly</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18300916-43-crimeloc232" type="placeName" value="St. James'-street, Piccadilly"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18300916-43-crimeloc232" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-43-off230 t18300916-43-crimeloc232"></join>; he put his hand into five different peoples' pockets - it was the evening of the King's birth-day; I then saw him take this handkerchief from the pocket of a person who I did not know - I followed him with two other officers; I had seen him put the handkerchief into his trousers - we took him, and found it on him at the watch-house; I could not find the gentleman he took it from - I asked the prisoner if there were any marks on it - he said No, but I found three large letters on it; I found two other handkerchief on him, both marked, though he said they were not.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I said it was not marked that I knew of.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18300916-43-verdict233" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18300916-43-verdict233" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 22. - <rs id="t18300916-43-punish234" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18300916-43-punish234" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-43-defend470 t18300916-43-punish234"></join>
               Transported for Life
            </rs>.</p>
